  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nCurrently forge raises error when contract name is omitted. \r\n\r\n```\r\nðŸ’¤ forge inspect src/Counter.sol abi --pretty\r\nerror: invalid value 'src/Counter.sol' for '<CONTRACT>': contract source info format must be `<path>:<contractname>` or `<contractname>`\r\n\r\nFor more information, try '--help'.\r\n```\r\n\r\nProposal is to automatically retrieve the contract name from the .sol file if there is just one contract defined within the file. \r\n\r\n\r\nCurrent convenience workaround - one can just type a contract name, however path can be tabbed into, which is faster / less typo prone. \r\n\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
